      <description>About Me Born and raised in Syria, my family and I fled to Lebanon in 2012 due to the Syrian Civil War. After graduating high school in Lebanon, I moved to the U.S., where I&amp;rsquo;m currently seeking asylum.
I am a second-year physics Ph.D. student at Stanford University. I am co-advised by Prof. Chao-Lin Kuo and Prof. Susan Clark at the Kavli Institute for Particle Astrophysics and Cosmology (KIPAC) at Stanford.</description>
